  "prompt": "If my ATM card is blocked for online transactions then how do i restart it?",
  "response": "If your ATM card is blocked for online transactions, here are some steps you can take to resolve the issue:\n\n1. **Contact Customer Service**: Call the customer service number of your bank. This number is usually found on the back of your ATM card or on the bank's website. Speak to a representative who can assist you.\n\n2. **Verify Your Identity**: Be prepared to verify your identity. This may involve answering security questions, providing your account number, or confirming your personal information.\n\n3. **Understand the Reason**: Ask why your card has been blocked for online transactions. It could be due to suspicious activity, reaching a spending limit, or a request you made for blocking online transactions.\n\n4. **Request Reactivation**: If the block is temporary and can be lifted, request the customer service representative to reactivate your card for online transactions.\n\n5. **Use Online Banking**: If you have access to online banking, you may have the option to manage your card settings and potentially unblock your card without speaking directly to a representative.\n\n6. **Follow Security Procedures**: If your card was blocked due to suspicious activity, the bank may require you to verify recent transactions or change your PIN.\n\n7. **Visit a Bank Branch**: If you're unable to resolve the issue over the phone, visiting a physical branch of your bank can provide further assistance.\n\n8. **Follow Up**: Once your card is reactivated, make sure to monitor your account and ensure that you can make online transactions as expected.\n\nIf you believe your card was blocked in error, make sure to express that clearly when contacting your bank.",
